<!-- By Dependent Issues (Action) - DO NOT REMOVE -->
This section is currently the same as the previous one; can we merge them?

I'd be inclined to merge these into a single
```lean
/-- See also `egauge_prod_mk` for when this bound is tight. -/
lemma le_egauge_prod (s : Set E) (t : Set F) (a : E) (b : F) :
    max (egauge 𝕜 s a) (egauge 𝕜 t b) ≤ egauge 𝕜 (s ×ˢ t) (a, b) :=
```
which is all you end up needing below anyway
Could yo uadd an `egauge_pi_univ` shorthand in terms of `Finite`, for convenience?
There is `egauge_univ_pi` above (I should fix its doc string).
Oh, I expected them to be in the other order.
`egauge_univ_pi` doesn't assume that `K` is a nontrivially normed field, just a normed division ring.
Am I right in thinking this is written as `[(𝓝[≠] (0 : 𝕜)).NeBot]`?
Maybe we should just define `NontriviallyNormedDivisionRing`? Though probably we should let the dust settle after #22842 first.

Perhaps
```suggestion
See also `egauge_univ_pi` for when `s = univ`, and `egauge_pi'` for a version with more choices of the technical assumptions.
```
I pushed this small change, which is more lines but fewer lemma invocations. Maybe there's a way to clean this up a little further.
(I used the ideas from your old proofs to make #23287)

```suggestion
See also `egauge_univ_pi` for when `s = univ`,
and `egauge_pi'` for a version with more choices of the technical assumptions.
```

pullRequest.title: feat(EGauge): add `egauge_pi` and `egauge_prod`
